    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-04-25T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-04-25T12:00:00-05:00" n="374"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/836: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-25T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 25, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 25—3:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. My 56, April 24, 11 a.m. For your information it appears that the Government
                    made every effort to save the lives of the two Generals executed yesterday but
                    that the control of such matters has been assumed by a group of officers whom it
                    dares not antagonize.… The motive actuating these officers appears to be revenge
                    for the six<note n="4" xml:id="d374fn4">Apparently a reference to the six chief
                        political leaders executed November 28, 1922; see <ref
                            target="frus1922v02#pg_412">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1922, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 412</ref>.</note> and strong support is
                    provided by an influential group of Greek Royalist Society. Unless the
                    Government soon regains the power to control these people there seems little to
                    prevent a repetition of the events of 1922.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
